Use MAUI's **lifecycle events** (`OnSleep`/`OnResume`) paired with `Preferences` for lightweight storage.

**1. In your `App.xaml.cs`** — broadcast lifecycle events:

```csharp
protected override void OnSleep()
{
    MessagingCenter.Send<App>(this, "AppSleep");
}

protected override void OnResume()
{
    MessagingCenter.Send<App>(this, "AppResume");
}
```

**2. In your notes page** — save/restore the draft:

```csharp
public partial class NotesPage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "notes_draft";

    public NotesPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "AppSleep", _ => SaveDraft());
        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "AppResume", _ => RestoreDraft());

        // Restore on first load too
        RestoreDraft();
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    // Clear draft when the user explicitly saves
    public void OnSaveClicked(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        // ... persist note to DB/file ...
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "AppSleep");
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "AppResume");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **When to save** | `OnSleep` — fires when app backgrounds |
| **When to restore** | `OnResume` + page constructor (cold start) |
| **Storage** | `Preferences` — fast, synchronous, ideal for small text |
| **Cleanup** | Remove the draft key after an explicit save |
| **Unsubscribe** | In `OnDisappearing` to avoid leaks |

> **Note:** `MessagingCenter` is deprecated in .NET 8+. If targeting newer MAUI, use the `WeakReferenceMessenger` from the **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** NuGet package instead — same pattern, just swap `MessagingCenter.Send/Subscribe` for `WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send/Register`.
